org.apache.chemistry.opencmis.client

Class SessionParameterMap

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.AbstractMap<K,V>
      • java.util.HashMap<K,V>
        • java.util.LinkedHashMap<String,String>
          • org.apache.chemistry.opencmis.client.SessionParameterMap
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Cloneable, Map<String,String>

    public class SessionParameterMap
extends LinkedHashMap<String,String>
    A map with convenience methods to set session parameters.

    Sample code: 

     SessionFactory factory = ...
 
 SessionParameterMap parameter = new SessionParameterMap();
 
 parameter.setBasicAuthentication("Otto", "****");
 parameter.setAtomPubBindingUrl("http://localhost/cmis/atom");
 parameter.setRepositoryId("myRepository");
 ...
 Session session = factory.createSession(parameter);
    See Also:
    SessionParameter, SessionFactory, Serialized Form

                                   String clientId,
                                   String clientSecret,
                                   String code,
                                   String redirectUri)
        Turns OAuth 2.0 authentication on and basic authentication and UsernameToken authentication off.

        This authentication method requests a new token and refreshes the token when it expires.

        Parameters:
        tokenEntpoint - the token endpoint URL
        clientId - the client ID
        clientSecret - the client secret if required, null otherwise
        code - the authorization code
        redirectUri - the redirect URI if required, null otherwise

      • setOAuthAuthentication

        public void setOAuthAuthentication(String tokenEntpoint,
                                   String clientId,
                                   String clientSecret,
                                   String accessToken,
                                   String refreshToken,
                                   long expirationTimestamp)
        Turns OAuth 2.0 authentication on and basic authentication and UsernameToken authentication off.

        This authentication method uses the provided token and refreshes the token when it expires.

        Parameters:
        tokenEntpoint - the token endpoint URL
        clientId - the client ID
        clientSecret - the client secret if required, null otherwise
        accessToken - the bearer access token
        refreshToken - the refresh token
        expirationTimestamp - the timestamp when the access token expires
